<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="225" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1250,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1358,1383]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head yellow, ocelli reddish, eyes brown, antennae yellow. Mesosoma light yellow. Fore wing hyaline. Legs light yellow to pale. Gaster light yellow, apices of stylets blackish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1250,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1430,1455]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Structure.</emphasis>
Head not wider than mesosoma, about 
<number box="[778,813,1430,1454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.4">1.4</number>
× as wide as high. Frontovertex about 
<number box="[1257,1293,1430,1454]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.6">0.6</number>
× as wide as head. Eye about as long as cheek. Distance between toruli about 
<number box="[918,954,1466,1490]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.6">0.6</number>
× as long as distance from torulus to eye margin. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[372,439,1502,1526]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1530,1553]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,348,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,339,1507]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Encarsia albata, sp. n., female: 1, antenna; 2, marginal vein; 3, mid tarsus; 4, ovipositor." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221953/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[427,439,1502,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) inserted under level of lower margin of eyes. Antennal radicle 
<number box="[1189,1225,1502,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="2.4">2.4</number>
× as long as wide. Scape about 
<number box="[293,307,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="4.0">4</number>
× as long as wide. Pedicel 
<number box="[603,638,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.7">1.7</number>
× as long as wide and 
<number box="[884,919,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.5">1.5</number>
× as long as first funicle segment. First funicle segment about 
<number box="[321,356,1574,1598]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.4">1.4</number>
× as long as wide, second and third segments subequal in length, 
<number box="[1092,1127,1574,1598]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.6">1.6</number>
× and 
<number box="[1198,1233,1574,1598]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="1.4">1.4</number>
× as long as wide, respectively. Club 
<number box="[359,371,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="3.0">3</number>
-segmented, slightly wider and longer than funicle. Flagellum with segments 
<number box="[1233,1275,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
each with one longitudinal sensillum. Mid lobe of mesoscutum with 
<number box="[759,773,1646,1670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="4.0">4</number>
pairs of setae, placed symmetrically. Scutellum about 
<number box="[1385,1421,1646,1670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.8">0.8</number>
× as long as mid lobe of mesoscutum and about 
<number box="[703,739,1682,1706]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.7">0.7</number>
× as wide as long. Scutellar placoid sensilla widely spaced. Anterior pair of scutellar setae slightly shorter than posterior pair, and distance between bases of anterior setae about 
<number box="[221,257,1754,1778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.7">0.7</number>
× as long as the distance between bases of posterior setae. Fore wing uniformly setose and 
<number box="[1287,1300,1754,1778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="3.0">3</number>
× as long as maximum width of wing, marginal fringe 
<number box="[627,663,1790,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.3">0.3</number>
× as long as width of wing, base with 
<number box="[1094,1108,1790,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
setae. Marginal vein (
<figureCitation box="[1360,1428,1790,1814]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1530,1553]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,348,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,339,1507]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Encarsia albata, sp. n., female: 1, antenna; 2, marginal vein; 3, mid tarsus; 4, ovipositor." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221953/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[1413,1428,1790,1814]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number box="[208,222,1826,1850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="6.0">6</number>
setae along anterior margin. Marginal fringe of hind wing about as long as maximum width of wing. Tarsal formula 
<number box="[249,264,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
- 
<number box="[273,288,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
- 
<number box="[297,312,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="5.0">5</number>
. Mid tibial spur 
<number box="[507,543,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.8">0.8</number>
× as long as basitarsus of mid tarsus (
<figureCitation box="[981,1052,1862,1886]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1530,1553]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,348,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,339,1507]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Encarsia albata, sp. n., female: 1, antenna; 2, marginal vein; 3, mid tarsus; 4, ovipositor." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221953/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[1036,1052,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1284,1862,1886]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1530,1553]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,348,1504]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,339,1507]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Encarsia albata, sp. n., female: 1, antenna; 2, marginal vein; 3, mid tarsus; 4, ovipositor." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221953/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<number box="[1269,1284,1862,1886]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) not exerted, about as long as mid tibia. Third valvula about 
<number box="[680,716,1898,1922]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" value="0.5">0.5</number>
× as long as second valvifer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1250,2031]" box="[199,375,1934,1958]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Male unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="226" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1250,2031]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="226" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1970,1995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[342,523,1971,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Encarsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[342,523,1971,1995]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">Encarsia albata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[530,594,1971,1995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[530,594,1971,1995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Myartseva &amp; Evans" authorityName="Myartseva &amp; Evans" box="[742,1074,1970,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Encarsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pitilla">
<emphasis box="[742,840,1971,1995]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="225">E. pitilla</emphasis>
Myartseva &amp; Evans
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the following complex of characters: mesosoma and gaster light yellow versus with infuscate parts; mid lobe of mesoscutum with 
<number box="[354,368,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="8.0">8</number>
versus 
<number box="[454,495,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
setae; base of fore wing with 
<number box="[831,845,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="5.0">5</number>
versus 
<number box="[931,987,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12</number>
setae, marginal vein with 
<number box="[1281,1295,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="6.0">6</number>
versus 
<number box="[1380,1436,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
setae along anterior margin; midtibial spur 
<number box="[654,690,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="0.8">0.8</number>
× versus subequal in length to basitarsus; and third valvula 
<number box="[1385,1421,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="0.5">0.5</number>
× versus 
<number box="[229,314,223,247]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3</number>
× as long as second valvifer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1107,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" box="[199,1107,260,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="226">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species named is based on the very light, pale color of the body.
</paragraph>
